<TEXT>
in his first trip abroad since leaving 
office former president reagan will visit england next month to 
give a lecture and visit the queen and prime minister margaret 
thatcher a spokeswoman said tuesday 
reagan will deliver the churchill lecture june 13 at londons 
ancient guildhall as the guest of the english speaking union an 
international volunteer organization devoted to promoting 
friendship and educational programs 
the lecture is named after former prime minister winston 
churchill who once was the groups chairman 
reagan will be accompanied by his wife nancy in london the 
reagans will have lunch with queen elizabeth ii and her husband 
prince phillip and dine with thatcher at 10 downing street said 
reagan spokeswoman paula franklin 
it will be the reagans first trip abroad since returning to 
california on jan 20 the day he retired from the presidency after 
two terms in office 
nancy and i are looking forward to renewing our friendship 
with her majesty the queen and with prime minister thatcher 
reagan said in a statement released by his office 
there has always been a very special relationship between the 
united states and the united kingdom and i am deeply honored to 
have been invited to deliver the churchill lecture reagan said 
we have many fond memories of our visits to london and are very 
happy to have an opportunity to again be in the company of our 
friends there soon 
</TEXT>
