<TEXT>
the fbi is investigating allegations that 
arizona state university campus police bullied black students while 
breaking up a brawl last month officials said 
university police chief doug bartosh said friday that agent dave 
small of the fbis phoenix bureau called him that week to tell him 
his department would be investigated 
small said the fbi has begun an investigation into possible 
civil rights violations but would not say what the focus of the 
probe was 
we welcome the investigation said bartosh i feel our 
officers acted appropriately based on the information i have 
asu police came under fire for their handling of the april 16 
brawl on fraternity row in which an unruly group of white students 
began yelling racial slurs at four black students who drove into 
the conflict 
