<TEXT>
pope john paul ii today beatified a 
19th century french missionary considered the apostle of the slaves 
brought to this island saying he should inspire islanders to fight 
todays slavery of materialism 
the pope celebrated a beatification mass on the palmfringed 
esplanade of the notre dame of the trinity church the crowd was 
estimated at up to 200000 twofifths of the entire population of 
this volcanic indian ocean island 
french prime minister michel rocard wearing a straw hat to ward 
off the tropical sun headed the official french delegation at the 
ceremony reunion has been a french overseas territory since 1946 
the pope arrived on the island monday night after a threeday 
visit to the african island of madagascar the first stop of his 
nineday pilgrimage he headed later today to zambia traveling for 
the first time on the concorde 
he is to visit malawi later in the week and return to rome 
saturday 
the beatification represented a first step towards possible 
sainthood for jeanbernard rousseau known as brother scubilion 
who died in 1867 at the age of 70 born in burgundy and baptized 
secretly during the french revolution rousseau joined the brother 
of the christian schools and moved to this island then known as 
bourbon in 1833 
he remained 34 years until his death devoting himself to 
teaching catechism to the african slaves brought to the island by 
the french colonists to work the coffee plantations 
described by local church officials as a nonviolent 
subversive he is credited with helping create the climate for 
the abolishment of slavery in 1848 
about 70 percent of reunions current population are descended 
from the slaves ninety percent of the population is roman catholic 
brother scubilion is a remarkable witness of the movement for 
holiness begun on this island by the first missionaries the 
whiterobed pope said in his homily in french he enlightened 
others with the light of jesus christ by his example and 
especially by his catechism among the slaves 
he helped them to gain confidence to give meaning to their 
lives to march toward hope and he distinguished himself in the 
service to the sick showing much compassion for his brothers in 
distress 
john paul said todays catholics in reunion should follow 
brother scubilions example and build a society more respectful 
of human dignity without being afraid of saying no to the slavery 
of materialism that could seduce you 
on your island you enjoy a relative abundance he said 
at the same time the race to consumerism can lead away from the 
real evangelist path 
reunion covering 970 square miles is the most prosperous of 
the four stops on the popes trip its economy is based on sugar 
exports and tourism and the per capita income is 3500 compared 
to only a few hundred dollars in the other countries 
earlier today the pope met with a group of youths in the garden 
of the residence of the local bishops he cautioned them not to be 
seeduced by secularization pornography casual sex and the 
temptation of magic 
he did not elaborate on that topic but local church officials 
have expressed concern about the spread of superstition fetishism 
exorcism and satanic cults 
 
