<TEXT>
seven people poached nearly 2 million worth of 
giant clams by underreporting harvests and evading state fisheries 
agents a prosecutor claimed 
in opening statements monday assistant prosecutor marilyn 
brenneman said the defendants routinely took thousands of pounds 
of state resources from puget sound without paying for them 
