president daniel arap moi has replaced his 
vice president in a shakeup that leaves kenyas major tribe out of 
the governments top two jobs for the first time since independence 
moi named george saitoti the finance minister and a former 
professor of mathematics at the university of nairobi as the 
countrys sixth vice president since this former british colony won 
black rule 25 years ago 
he replaces josephat karanja who resigned as vice president and 
vice chairman of the ruling party after receiving a unanimous vote 
of no confidence from parliament saitoti retains the finance 
portfolio 
