todays casualties raised the overall toll to 278 people killed 
and 1010 wounded since march 8 when fighting broke out between 
aouns christian army units and an alliance of syrian and druse 
forces 
a police spokesman said syrian gunners targeted the coastal 
strip north of beirut and prevented the french tanker penhors from 
approaching the power station in the suburb of zouk to unload fuel 
oil 
the barrage damaged the main power cable connecting the zouk 
plant with beirut and stripped the capital of its daily twohour 
ration of electricity said the police spokesman who cannot be 
named under standing rules 
the christian voice of lebanon radio blamed the ceasefire 
violation on syrian gunners and said aouns troops responded in 
selfdefense 
voice of the people radio of the prosyrian lebanese communist 
party blamed aoun for the renewed fighting 
aouns gunners started the barrage the radio said without 
elaboration 
the thuds of exploding shells echoed across beirut and the 
flashes of artillery explosions lighted up the dark skies most 
civilians deserted their apartments and sought refuge in 
underground shelters 
the police spokesman said there was almost no traffic in beirut 
as the warring factions traded sniper fire and rocketpropelled 
grenades across the green line that divides the christian and 
moslem sectors 
it seems most civilians have decided to remain in basements 
and bomb shelters pending the outcome of ibrahimis mission the 
spokesman said 
ibrahimi was to meet wednesday with acting premier salim hoss 
head of the moslem cabinet in lebanons dual government and 
complete arrangements for the deployment of arab military observers 
to oversee a new truce 
an aide to hoss said ibrahimi and the sunni moslem leader will 
discuss a compromise to the sticking point of the truce aouns 
blockade of ports run by syrianbacked militias south of beirut 
the compromise calls for the deployment of arab observers at the 
ports to guarantee that they are not used for illegal 
activities said the aide who spoke on condition of anonymity 
the aide said it was ibrahimis responsibility to convince druse 
warlord walid jumblatt and shiite moslem leader nabih berri to 
accept the proposed solution 
berris shiite amal militia operates a singledock harbor in 
beiruts fishermens suburb of ouzai and jumblatts progressive 
socialist party runs two facilities at khaldeh and jiyeh south of 
the capital 
aoun on march 6 blockaded the three facilities that deny the 
state treasury of about 100 million in lost customs dues annually 
aoun also said the ports were used to smuggle drugs and 
terrorism 
jumblatts forces responded to aouns blockade by shelling the 
310squaremile christian enclave northeast of the capital syrian 
gunners later joined in the fighting but amal did not take part 
aoun and other christian leaders accuse the syrians of failing 
to achieve a 1976 peacekeeping mandate from the arab league by 
siding with the moslems in lebanons 14yearold civil war 
</TEXT>
