was assigned the interpreter monday because of a settlement reached 
in october of a lawsuit 
the council for the deaf sued los angeles county in 1981 for 
refusing to pay the 4000 shapiro spent to hire an interpreter to 
help him serve as a juror in 1980 hearing impairment had been a 
valid excuse for being excused from jury duty 
