central texas town was closed for more than 14 hours after the 
truck carrying eight rocket pods loaded with six rockets each ran 
off the road authorities said 
explosives experts from fort hood and fort sill okla worked 
for more than three hours to remove the rockets each of which 
carried 644 m77 grenades said officials with the texas department 
of public safety 
the rockets were not armed and posed no danger said david 
harris spokesman for the us army missile command near 
huntsville ala 
part of the development program involved taking fully loaded 
rockets and dropping them 20 to 30 feet onto concrete to see if 
they could withstand that kind of impact harris said 
officials evacuated one resident of a mobile home located about 
200 yards from the accident site but allowed her to return seven 
hours later police sgt don willingham said 
the driver and a passenger suffered minor injuries police said 
all i know is i saw a deer and i swerved to miss it said 
