in rome chancellor helmut kohl of west germany said he was open 
to reasonable compromise but wants talks to begin soon the 
united states and britain have rejected such negotiations 
kohl however expressed hope the allies could reach a unified 
position on the issue during a summit at the end of this month he 
said nato could negotiate on the battlefield weapons at the same 
time it discusses strategic arms conventional forces and chemical 
weapons 
the comments came after a meeting with premier ciriaco de mita 
who said italy supports linking the proposed talks on reducing the 
shortrange nuclear weapons to progress in conventional arms talks 
in paris foreign ministers roland dumas of france and 
