as a crippling strike at eastern airlines heads 
into its third month the carriers unions say they remain solid 
although some employees union and management are bailing out 
karen ceremsak a company spokeswoman cant estimate how many 
of easterns 12000 nonunion employees have taken other jobs since 
the march 4 strike by the companys machinists pilots and flight 
attendants virtually grounded the airline 
as more time passes more people will go on to other things 
she said 
