the government reported tuesday that orders to 
us factories for manufactured goods increased 07 percent in 
march but analysts still saw signs in the report that the economy 
was cooling off 
orders for durable and nondurable goods rose to a seasonally 
adjusted 2329 billion in march after dropping 2 percent in 
february and 12 percent in january the commerce department 
reported 
the gain last month was propelled by a big jump in 
transportation orders which surged 101 percent on the strength of 
a 483 percent increase in orders for aircraft missiles and parts 
excluding transportation a category that is subject to wide 
swings depending on when big contracts are signed all other orders 
were down 09 percent in march after declining 1 percent in 
february 
analysts said the report added to signs that economic growth is 
slackening but also demonstrated the economy still has some 
strength left 
i dont think the economy is as weak as some of the recent 
