programs and a 25 percent decline in steel operating income 
reported a firstquarter profit tuesday of 766 million down 
sharply from a year earlier excluding a onetime charge 
in the first quarter of 1988 the dallasbased conglomerate 
suffered a net loss of 212 billion but that period included a 
onetime charge of 226 billion resulting from a change in 
accounting for postemployment medical and life insurance benefits 
without the charge ltvs income for the first quarter of 1988 
was 1312 million 
first quarter sales declined to 16 billion from 19 billion 
in the first quarter in 1988 sales results for the companys steel 
bar division were being held for disposition 
sales declines in aircraft and energy products were offset by 
higher sales in missiles and electronics 
in releasing its first quarter earnings the company said cost 
increases are expected in its ya7f aircraft development program 
and higher unit costs are projected on production of boeing 747 
commercial aircraft components 
the decline in first quarter sales and operating income 
reflects ltvs continuing rationalization of steel operations and 
the cost increases in the two aircraft programs said raymond a 
hay chairman and chief executive officer 
ltv attributed the decline in steel operating income to the sale 
last year of its warren ohio steel plant 
demand for flat rolled steel remained firm most of our 
facilities are operating at a high percentage of capacity and 
orders are strong through the second quarter hay said 
