<TEXT>
browningferris industries inc one of the 
nations largest trash haulers said tuesday it reached an 
agreement to supply plastic refuse to the nations largest plastics 
recycling company 
under the agreement bfi will ship plastics from its curbside 
collection programs recycling program and processing centers to 
wellman incs facilities in south carolina and pennsylvania 
officials said 
this will serve everyones needs bfi chairman william d 
ruckelshaus said 
it is expected to guarantee an assured market for all the 
plastics we are collecting in our recycling programs now and as we 
expand to provide wellman a growing supply of plastics so they can 
continue to grow ruckelshaus said 
houstonbased bfi described the deal as the first of its kind 
between a major waste service and a recycling company 
terms of the agreement were not disclosed 
wellman with 1988 sales of 3146 million manufactures a 
variety of products from waste plastics and other materials its 
primary raw materials are reclaimed soft drink bottles 
we have long maintained that the key to effective plastic 
recycling lies primarily in establishing an effective and efficient 
collection program wellman president tom duff said since 
bfis interest is also businessdriven we are confident that this 
joint effort will be successful 
bfi which has been involved in recycling since 1971 operates 
curbside recovery programs that include yard wastes paper metal 
and glass containers plastics and oil the company also operates 
recycleries where materials for recycling are extracted from 
waste and where other materials are collected from the public 
bfi also is involved in municipal and commercial sweeping 
operations medical waste services portable restroom services and 
asbestos abatement 
